Odor is a much stronger factor in telling poisonous and edible mushrooms apart. 
Certain smells show up almost only in poisonous mushrooms, while cap color is mixed across both groups and isn’t as helpful. 
So for a scikit‑learn model, odor would likely be the more useful feature.
